  "pipeline": {
    "log_level": "normal",
    "jar": {
      "monthly_subscription_price_cents": 999,
      "_doc": "Prix abonnement Ratis mensuel en centimes. Définit le seuil 100% de la jauge JarPrestige (= prestige). Valeur par défaut 9.99€ à valider PO."
    },
    "anti_fraud": {
      "_doc": "Anti-fraud receipt-pipeline V1 thresholds (validated PO 2026-05-11, cf ARCH_receipt_pipeline.md § Réconciliation tickets). PR1 shipped the DDL ; PR2 (2026-05-11) activated phash_* keys via the pipeline phase 0 hook in worker/receipt_task.py ; PR3 (2026-05-11) activated the dual fingerprint compute + UNIQUE intra-user rescan ; PR4 (2026-05-11) activated cross-user policy (fp_window_hours + fp_fuzzy_match_threshold), daily caps (receipts_max_per_day_per_user + receipts_soft_warn_per_day) and device-pattern (device_fp_*) via worker/pipeline/persist.py + fraud_lookup.py ; PR5 (2026-05-11) activated rescan_max_attempts via routes/scan.py::post_scan_receipt_rescan (UPDATE atomique WHERE rescan_attempts<:cap, gated par pipeline.enabled) + admin queue routes/admin/fraud_suspicions.py. SPRINT COMPLET. Toggle enable_phash_check=false to roll the PR2 hook back. fp_fuzzy_match_threshold=8 is the 10-component scheme : 8/10 exact + Levenshtein ≤ 1 on numeric components (cf fuzzy_match_intra_user). Rollout flip = operator-driven via pipeline.enabled (toujours false en prod au moment du sprint-close).",
      "enable_phash_check": true,
      "receipts_max_per_day_per_user": 14,
      "receipts_soft_warn_per_day": 7,
      "rescan_max_attempts": 3,
      "phash_hamming_threshold": 8,
      "phash_window_days": 30,
      "fp_window_hours": 48,
      "fp_fuzzy_match_threshold": 8,
      "device_fp_distinct_users_threshold": 3,
      "device_fp_window_days": 30
    },
    "promo_detection": {
      "_doc": "Phase C-4 — regex layer detecting promo signals in raw OCR receipt text, post-comprehend. Bolt-on (does NOT modify the V3 LLM prompt or parsed_ticket schema). Fires one trigger_action(promo_found, quantity=N) per receipt where N = distinct signal count (dedup-by-pattern within a receipt). Enables 4 currently-ghost promo_found missions in the V1 catalogue (1 daily + 3 weekly). Patterns are Python regex compiled with re.IGNORECASE ; set enable=false to disable the entire detector without a code revert. Default 7 patterns cover Carrefour, Monoprix, Franprix shapes ; Auchan / Lidl variants out of scope until empirical tuning lands.",
      "enable": true,
      "patterns": [
        "\\bpromo\\b",
        "\\bremise\\b",
        "\\br[ée]duction\\b",
        "-\\s?\\d+(?:[,.]\\d+)?\\s?[€%]",
        "\\boffre\\b",
        "\\bsoldes?\\b",
        "\\b[ée]conomies?\\b\\s*:?\\s*\\d+"
      ]
    }
  },
